The paper deals with limit theorems in hidden Markov models, which are commonly used in information theory and statistics. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves probability theory and statistical inference, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper applies the limit theorems to maximum likelihood estimation, which is a common technique in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
